WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:28.960
Chapter 58 Cry aloud, spare not, lift up thy voice

00:28.960 --> 00:36.780
like a trumpet, and show my people their transgression, and the house of Jacob, their sins. Yet they

00:36.780 --> 00:43.800
seek me daily, and delight to know my ways, as a nation that did righteousness, and forsook

00:43.800 --> 00:50.440
not the ordinance of their God. They ask of me the ordinances of justice, they take delight

00:50.440 --> 00:56.640
in approaching to God. Wherefore have we fasted, say they, and thou seest not? Wherefore have

00:56.640 --> 01:03.000
we afflicted our soul, and thou takest no knowledge? Behold, in the day of your fast,

01:03.460 --> 01:11.480
ye find pleasure, and exact all your labours. Behold, ye fast for strife and debate, and

01:11.480 --> 01:18.160
to smite with the fist of wickedness. Ye shall not fast as ye do this day, to make your voice

01:18.160 --> 01:24.480
to be heard on high. Is it such a fast that I have chosen, a day for a man to afflict

01:24.480 --> 01:31.220
his soul? Is it to bow down his head as a bulrush, and to spread sackcloth and ashes

01:31.220 --> 01:38.860
under him? Wilt thou call this a fast and an acceptable day to the Lord? Is not this

01:38.860 --> 01:45.020
the fast that I have chosen, to loose the bands of wickedness, to undo the heavy burdens,

01:45.260 --> 01:52.560
and to let the oppressed go free, and that ye break every yoke? Is it not to deal thy

01:52.560 --> 01:59.040
bread to the hungry, and that thou bring the poor that are cast out to thy house, when thou seest

01:59.040 --> 02:06.140
an acre that thou cover him, and that thou hide not thyself from thine own flesh? Then shall thy

02:06.140 --> 02:12.880
light break forth as the morning, and thine health shall spring forth speedily, and thy righteousness

02:12.880 --> 02:20.020
shall go before thee. The glory of the Lord shall be thy rear reward. Then shall thou call and the

02:20.020 --> 02:27.120
Lord shall answer. Thou shall cry, and he shall say, Here I am. If thou take away from the midst

02:27.120 --> 02:34.660
of thee the yoke, the putting forth of the finger, and speaking vanity, and if thou draw out thy soul

02:34.660 --> 02:42.600
to the hungry, and satisfy the afflicted soul, then shall thy light rise in obscurity, and thy

02:42.600 --> 02:50.680
darkness be as the noonday, and the Lord shall guide thee continually, and satisfy thy soul in

02:50.680 --> 02:58.920
drought, and make fat thy bones, and thou shall be like a watered garden, and like a spring of water

02:58.920 --> 03:05.800
whose waters fail not, and they that shall be of thee shall build the old waste places.

03:06.360 --> 03:12.280
Thou shalt raise up the foundations of many generations, and thou shalt be called the

03:12.280 --> 03:20.120
repairer of the breach, the restorer of paths to dwelling. If thou turn away thy foot from the

03:20.120 --> 03:27.700
Sabbath, from doing thy pleasure on my holy day, and call the Sabbath the delight, the holy of the

03:27.700 --> 03:35.880
Lord, honorable, and shalt honor him, not doing thine own ways, nor finding thine own pleasure,

03:36.380 --> 03:44.120
nor speaking thine own words, then shalt thou delight thyself in the Lord, and I will cause

03:44.120 --> 03:51.500
thee to ride upon the high places of the earth, and feed thee with the heritage of Jacob thy father,

03:51.500 --> 03:59.220
for the mouth of the Lord hath spoken it. Chapter 59 Behold, the Lord's hand is not

03:59.220 --> 04:06.740
shortened, that it cannot save, neither his ear heavy, that it cannot hear. But your iniquities

04:06.740 --> 04:12.720
have separated between you and your God, and your sins have hid his face from you,

04:12.860 --> 04:20.000
that he will not hear. For your hands are defiled with blood, and your fingers with iniquity.

04:20.000 --> 04:27.600
Your lips have spoken lies, your tongue hath muttered perverseness. None calleth for justice,

04:28.060 --> 04:35.800
nor any pleadeth for truth. They trust in vanity, and speak lies. They conceive mischief,

04:35.840 --> 04:43.460
and bring forth iniquity. They hatch cockatrice eggs, and weave the spider's web. He that eateth

04:43.460 --> 04:50.480
their eggs dieth, and that which is crushed breaketh out into a viper. Their webs shall

04:50.480 --> 04:56.580
not become garments, neither shall they cover themselves with their works. Their works are

04:56.580 --> 05:03.160
works of iniquity, and the act of violence is in their hands. Their feet run to evil,

05:03.460 --> 05:09.500
and they make haste to shed innocent blood. Their thoughts are thoughts of iniquity.

05:09.500 --> 05:17.000
Wasting and destruction are in their paths. The way of peace they know not, and there is no

05:17.000 --> 05:24.480
judgment in their goings. They have made them crooked paths. Whosoever goeth therein shall not

05:24.480 --> 05:32.330
know peace. Therefore is judgment far from us. Neither doth justice overtake us. We wait for

05:32.330 --> 05:40.010
light, but behold obscurity, for brightness, but we walk in darkness. We grope for the wall

05:40.010 --> 05:47.830
like the blind, and we grope as if we had no eyes. We stumble at noonday as in the night.

05:48.350 --> 05:57.430
We are in desolate places as dead men. We roar all like bears, and mourn sore like doves.

05:57.430 --> 06:04.170
We look for judgment, but there is none, for salvation, but it is far off from us.

06:04.650 --> 06:11.650
For our transgressions are multiplied before thee, and our sins testify against us. For our

06:11.650 --> 06:18.230
transgressions are with us, and as for our iniquities we know them, in transgressing and

06:18.230 --> 06:25.490
lying against the Lord, and departing away from our God. Speaking oppression and revolt,

06:25.490 --> 06:32.790
conceiving and uttering from the heart words of falsehood. And judgment is turned away backward,

06:33.350 --> 06:41.410
and justice standeth afar off. For truth is fallen in the street, and equity cannot enter.

06:42.190 --> 06:50.050
Yea, truth faileth, and he that departeth from evil maketh himself a prey. And the Lord saw it,

06:50.050 --> 06:56.550
and it displeased him that there was no judgment. And he saw that there was no man, and wondered

06:56.550 --> 07:04.190
that there was no intercessor. Therefore his arm brought salvation unto him, and his righteousness

07:04.190 --> 07:12.110
it sustained him. For he put on righteousness as a breastplate, and a helmet of salvation upon his

07:12.110 --> 07:19.090
head. And he put on the garments of vengeance for clothing, and was clad with zeal as a cloak.

07:19.090 --> 07:27.370
According to their deeds, accordingly he will repay. Fury to his adversaries, recompense to

07:27.370 --> 07:34.350
his enemies. To the islands he will repay recompense. So shall they fear the name of the

07:34.350 --> 07:41.250
Lord from the west, and his glory from the rising of the sun. When the enemy shall come in like a

07:41.250 --> 07:47.110
flood, the Spirit of the Lord shall lift up a standard against him. And the Redeemer shall

07:47.110 --> 07:53.630
come to Zion, and unto them that turn from transgression in Jacob, saith the Lord.

07:54.210 --> 08:00.770
As for me, this is my covenant with them, saith the Lord. My Spirit that is upon thee,

08:01.190 --> 08:07.390
and my words which I have put in thy mouth, shall not depart out of thy mouth, nor out of the mouth

08:07.390 --> 08:14.770
of thy seed, nor out of the mouth of thy seed's seed, saith the Lord, from henceforth and for ever.

08:15.570 --> 08:25.230
Chapter 60 Arise, shine, for thy light is come, and the glory of the Lord is risen upon thee.

08:25.770 --> 08:32.730
For behold, the darkness shall cover the earth, and gross darkness the people, but the Lord shall

08:32.730 --> 08:40.410
arise upon thee, and his glory shall be seen upon thee. And the Gentiles shall come to thy light,

08:40.410 --> 08:46.910
and kings to the brightness of thy rising. Lift up thine eyes round about and see,

08:47.370 --> 08:55.110
all they gather themselves together, they come to thee. Thy sons shall come from far, and thy

08:55.110 --> 09:02.390
daughters shall be nursed at thy side. Then thou shalt see and flow together, and thine heart shall

09:02.390 --> 09:08.790
fear and be enlarged. Because the abundance of the sea shall be converted unto thee,

09:08.790 --> 09:15.950
the forces of the Gentiles shall come unto thee. The multitude of camels shall cover thee,

09:16.270 --> 09:23.010
the dromedaries of Midian and Ephar, all they from Sheba shall come. They shall bring gold and

09:23.010 --> 09:29.730
incense, and they shall show forth the praises of the Lord. All the flocks of Kedar shall be gathered

09:29.730 --> 09:35.770
together unto thee, the rams of Nebeoth shall minister unto thee. They shall come up with

09:35.770 --> 09:43.730
acceptance on mine altar, and I will glorify the house of my glory. Who are these that fly as a

09:43.730 --> 09:50.670
cloud, and as the doves to their windows? Surely the Isles shall wait for me, and the ships of

09:50.670 --> 09:58.310
Tarshish first, to bring thy sons from far, their silver and their gold with them, unto the name of

09:58.310 --> 10:06.230
the Lord thy God, and to the Holy One of Israel, because he hath glorified thee. And the sons of

10:06.230 --> 10:13.790
strangers shall build up thy walls, and their kings shall minister unto thee. For in my wrath

10:13.790 --> 10:21.190
I smote thee, but in my favor have I had mercy on thee. Therefore thy gates shall be open

10:21.630 --> 10:28.510
continually. They shall not be shut day nor night, that men may bring unto thee the forces of the

10:28.510 --> 10:34.650
Gentiles, and that their kings may be brought. For the nation and kingdom that will not serve

10:34.650 --> 10:42.230
thee shall perish, yea, those nations shall be utterly wasted. The glory of Lebanon shall

10:42.230 --> 10:50.330
come unto thee, the fir tree, the pine tree, and the box together, to beautify the place of my

10:50.330 --> 10:57.530
sanctuary, and I will make the place of my feet glorious. The sons also of them that afflicted

10:57.530 --> 11:04.370
thee shall come bending unto thee, and all they that despised thee shall bow themselves down at

11:04.370 --> 11:11.970
the soles of thy feet, and they shall call thee the city of the Lord, the Zion of the Holy One of

11:11.970 --> 11:19.670
Israel. Whereas thou hast been forsaken and hated, so that no man went through thee, I will make thee

11:19.670 --> 11:28.350
an eternal excellency, a joy of many generations. Thou shalt also suck the milk of the Gentiles,

11:28.570 --> 11:35.110
and shalt suck the breast of kings, and thou shalt know that I the Lord, and thy Savior,

11:35.470 --> 11:43.350
and thy Redeemer, the mighty one of Jacob. For brass I will bring gold, and for iron

11:43.350 --> 11:52.150
I will bring silver, and for wood brass, and for stones iron. I will also make thy officers

11:52.150 --> 11:59.610
peace, and thine exactors righteousness. Violence shall no more be heard in thy land,

12:00.130 --> 12:07.150
wasting nor destruction within thy borders, but thou shalt call thy walls salvation,

12:07.150 --> 12:15.310
and thy gates praise. The sun shall be no more thy light by day, neither for brightness

12:15.310 --> 12:21.890
shall the moon give light unto thee, but the Lord shall be unto thee an everlasting light,

12:22.290 --> 12:29.890
and thy God thy glory. Thy sun shall no more go down, neither shall thy moon withdraw itself,

12:30.310 --> 12:35.970
for the Lord shall be thy everlasting light, and the days of thy morning shall be ended.

12:35.970 --> 12:43.510
Thy people also shall be all righteous, they shall inherit the land forever, the branch of

12:43.510 --> 12:51.850
my planting, the work of my hands, that I may be glorified. A little one shall become a thousand,

12:52.190 --> 12:59.950
and a small one a strong nation. I the Lord will hasten it in his time.

13:06.510 --> 13:07.210
you

